Object.Field: Specifies a string that indicates the date format to use when writing dates or timestamps. Custom date formats follow the formats at java.text.SimpleDateFormat. This applies to both DateType and TimestampType. If None is set, it uses the default value, yyyy-MM-dd.

Specifies a string that indicates the timestamp format to use when writing dates or timestamps. Custom date formats follow the formats at java.text.SimpleDateFormat. This applies to both DateType and TimestampType. If None is set, it uses the default value, yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSXXX.
String representation of a null value.
Sets the string representation of a null value. If None is set, it uses the default value, empty string. Since 2.0.1, this nullValue param applies to all supported types including the string type.

This KM option allows adding custom store options. Any valid Spark option for the given format can be added here. Use the following syntax : '<option1>'='<value1>', '<option2>'='<value2>' ... These options will be appended to the list of principal store options.

Set this option to True if you are using generic SQL syntax for target attributes expressions. Set this option to False if you are using Spark Python syntax for target attributes expressions. NOTE: If this option is set to False (non-default), and expression is a constant - specify expression as lit(<my constant value>) Check pyspark.sql.functions module reference for more info about lit function: pyspark.sql.functions.lit(col) - Creates a Column of literal value.

If this option is set to True the column names and types will be inferred from source data and DataFrame will be created with default options. If it is set to False (default), DataFrame schema will be specified based on source datastore definition.
The sample ratio of rows used for inferring
If schema inference is needed, SAMPLING_RATIO is used to determined the ratio of rows used for schema inference. The first row will be used if SAMPLING_RATIO is not set.
